id: genio-mipi-camera/ap1302-ar0830-gstreamer-display
plugin: manual
category_id: genio-camera
imports:
    from com.canonical.plainbox import manifest
requires:
    manifest.is_Genio == 'True'
    manifest.has_vendor_specific_mipi_camera == 'True'
    manifest.has_genio_onsemi_ap1302_isp_and_ar0830_camera_module_as_yuv_sensor == 'True'
depends: genio-mipi-camera/firmware-checking-ap1302-ar0830
estimated_duration: 0.1
_summary: Onsemi AP1302 with AR0830 display the video streaming on panel or monitor
_purpose:
    Display the video streaming on panel or monitor
_steps:
    1. Install required packages if not already installed:
       sudo apt install v4l-utils gstreamer1.0-tools
    2. (If support v4l2 sensor), 
       Get the media node
       MEDIA_DEV=$(v4l2-ctl -z platform:$(basename `find /sys/bus/platform/devices/ -name "*camisp"`) --list-devices | grep media)
       Set camera capture format through media-ctl for CSI0
       media-ctl -d ${MEDIA_DEV} -l "'seninf-0':1 -> 'mtk-cam camsv-0':0 [5]"
       media-ctl -d ${MEDIA_DEV} -l "'ap1302.0-003c':2 -> 'seninf-0':0 [1]"
       media-ctl -d ${MEDIA_DEV} -V "'ap1302.0-003c':2 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/3840x2160 field:none]"
       media-ctl -d ${MEDIA_DEV} -V "'seninf-0':1 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/3840x2160 field:none]"
       media-ctl -d ${MEDIA_DEV} -V "'mtk-cam camsv-0':1 [fmt:UYVY8_1X16/3840x2160 field:none]"
    3. Find the AP1302-AR0830 camera video nodes:
       (If support ImgSensor)
       v4l2-ctl --list-devices | grep mtk-v4l2-camera -A 4
       (If support v4l2 sensor)
       VIDEO_DEV=(`for i in {0..5}; do media-ctl -d ${MEDIA_DEV} --entity "mtk-cam camsv-$i main-stream"; done | tr "\n" " "`)
       echo ${VIDEO_DEV[0]}
       Note: AP1302-AR0830 will only have 1 video node for Preview, Video, and Capture on the same node.
    4. (If support ImgSensor)Check supported formats for the capture node:
       v4l2-ctl -d /dev/videoX --list-formats-ext
    5. Preview a UYVY video for 5 seconds:
       timeout -s2 --preserve-status 5s gst-launch-1.0 v4l2src device=/dev/videoX io-mode=dmabuf \
         ! video/x-raw,width=3840,height=2160,format=UYVY,framerate=30/1 \
         ! waylandsink sync=false
_verification:
    1. Does the command can be performed wihtout any problem?
    2. The video streaming should be shown on panel
